CPE 480: Project
Twitter Meme Bot
Alex Ehm, Nupur Garg, Kyle Mulligan, Mason Stevenson, Jules Sulpico

Notes when running:

   Create a config.py file containing:

      consumer_key = 'CONSUMER_KEY_HERE'
      consumer_secret = 'CONSUMER_SECRET_HERE'
      access_token = 'ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE'
      access_secret = 'ACCESS_SECRET_HERE'

	For instructions on how to get access keys, go here: https://marcobonzanini.com/2015/03/02/mining-twitter-data-with-python-part-1/
	
Installation

   pip install nltk
   pip install pillow

Running tests (From project root):

   python -m unittest Twitter.TweetTest
   python -m unittest Filtering.FilterTest
   python -m unittest Memes.MemeClassTest
   python MemeGen/memegenerator.py test-text

Running program (From project root):

   Running Program
   
      python tweet_loader.py
      python generate_meme.py

   Generating Classifiers

      python Memes/classifiers/generate_questions_classifier.py 
